{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/npkill","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"2085fd33-508f-5a91-8f30-a0d03f8bb914","html":"<p>I have been holding lot of Github repositories based on ‚ÄúNPM‚Äù ecosystem, both personal and company projects on my machine. Each repository requires NPM install, obviously. The process takes some space, but since eventually it will be bundled on production I care less.\nAlso, on a different note, I end up backing up my photos to cloud storage from my SSD because of limited space (250 gb). Little did I know that real culprit of ‚ÄúHard disk space full‚Äù notification on my machine was JS Ecosystem. Lets check how much does each ‚Äúnode_module‚Äù folder cost.</p>\n<h2 id=\"npkill\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#npkill\" aria-label=\"npkill permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>NPKill</h2>\n<p>Here is an awesome tool - <a href=\"https://github.com/voidcosmos/npkill\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">NPKILL</a>, that exposes each ‚Äúnode_modules‚Äù folder in your system and helps you in the cleanup.</p>\n<p>This tool allows you to list any node_modules directories in your system, as well as the space they take up. You can then select which ones you want to erase to free up space. Yay!</p>\n<p>Obviously, you will have to install it using <code class=\"language-text\">npm install npkill -g</code>, which will create node_modules directory its dependency somewhere in the system üòÇüòú. Such is npm and JS ecosystem!</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/6c68b/npkill.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.16666666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/8ac56/npkill.webp 240w,\n/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/d3be9/npkill.webp 480w,\n/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/e46b2/npkill.webp 960w,\n/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/f992d/npkill.webp 1440w,\n/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/e4a01/npkill.webp 1888w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/8ff5a/npkill.png 240w,\n/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/e85cb/npkill.png 480w,\n/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/d9199/npkill.png 960w,\n/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/07a9c/npkill.png 1440w,\n/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/6c68b/npkill.png 1888w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/3574571fe3a0c3cff04917455952fb17/d9199/npkill.png\"\n          alt=\"Screenshot\"\n          title=\"Screenshot\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>As you can check out, 33 Gigs of node_modules. I removed all Github repos which require minimal maintenance and also learnt that in JS ecosystem, your developer machine should be treated like prod machine!</p>\n<p>NPKill has lot of options around directory to scan and some reporting settings. By default, npkill will scan for node_modules starting at the path where npkill command is executed.</p>\n<p>Official Site: <a href=\"https://github.com/voidcosmos/npkill\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">NPKILL</a></p>\n<hr>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/npkill","tagSlugs":["/tag/js-ecosystem/","/tag/cli/","/tag/tool/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-08-18T18:05:00.738Z","description":"CLI based Tool to show the disk space `node_modules` eating up in your machine.","tags":["JS Ecosystem","CLI","Tool"],"title":"NPKILL - Expose the heavy node_module folder on disk","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/npkill"}}}